What is a REST API

Also know as RESTful API, is an application programming interface(called API or web API) comforms
to the constraints of REST architectural style(REST stands for representational state transfer) allows for
interaction with RESTful web services.

API: set of definitions and protocols for building and integrating application software. a contract between
an information provider and an information user

the content required by the consumer(is the call)
the content required by the producer(the response)

example:
API design for a weather service
the call: user supply a zip code
the response: producer reply with high temp and low temp


What is REST?
a set of architectural constraints

client request is made via a RESTful API,
transfers a representation of the state of the resource to the requester.

This information, or representaion, is delivered in one of several formats via HTTP(HyperText Transfer Protocol):

JSON(Javascript Object Notation), HTML(HyperText Markup Language), Python, PHP




